Marathi PDF Summary Generator
This Flask application is designed to extract text from Marathi PDF files, generate summaries, and extract keywords. It uses various natural language processing techniques and libraries such as PyPDF2, Sumy, NLTK, langdetect, and Googletrans.


Installation :

To run this application locally, follow these steps:

Clone this repository to your local machine:

git clone https://github.com/Gauravyd2001/Gauravyd2001-MARATHI-PDF-SUMMARY-GENARTOR-.git
Navigate to the project directory:

cd Gauravyd2001-MARATHI-PDF-SUMMARY-GENARTOR-
Install the required dependencies. It's recommended to use a virtual environment:

DEPENDENCIES:

pip install -r requirements.txt

Start the Flask application:

python app.py
Open your web browser and go to http://localhost:5000/.

Upload a Marathi PDF file using the provided form.
The application will extract the text from the PDF, generate a summary, and display the result.

The project structure is as follows:
.
├── app.py                  # Main Flask application
├── uploads/                # Directory to store uploaded PDF files
├── templates/              # HTML templates for the Flask application
│   ├── index.html          # Home page template
│   └── result.html         # Result page template
├── static/                 # Static files (CSS, JS)
│   └── style.css           # CSS file for styling
├── README.md               # Project README file
└── requirements.txt        # List of Python dependencies

Dependencies:
Flask
PyPDF2
Sumy
NLTK
langdetect
googletrans


You can install these dependencies using pip:


pip install -r requirements.txt